<h2 id="section-top">Children's &amp; Adolescent Services</h2>
</div>
<div class="col four-sm">
</div>
<div class="col three-sm" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_contentColumn1">
<div class="box">
<p class="module">
        This Department is managed by  
        <a href="/Services/Trusts/Overview/DefaultView.aspx?id=967">Pennine Acute Hospitals NHS Trust</a>
</p>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div class="service-locations clear">
<div class="panel edit-box">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<p class="address"><br/>0161 624 0420</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<div id="imageContentab0d0a41d9514451b21b6d97507cc5d6">
</div>
<p><strong>Out patient services are provided at Fairfield General, North Manchester, Rochdale Infirmary and The Royal Oldham.  </strong></p>
<p><strong>In patient services are provided at North Manchester and The Royal Oldham only.  In addition to this, some out patient services are provided at Health Centres within the local community e.g. Ophthalmology, Audiology and Ear, Nose and Throat (ENT).</strong></p></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="panel name-thingsshouldknowmodule">
<div class="panel-content">
<div class="pad clear">
<h3>Things you should know</h3>
<p>The changes to maternity &amp; children's services at Fairfield General Hospital are part of the Making it Better programme, the reorganisation of children's &amp; maternity services across Greater Manchester to provide improved healthcare in the community and concentrate services in fewer, larger units.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
